  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this repeated measures design gait training study is to develop and
      quantitatively assess the effectiveness of a virtual reality training environment using
      real-time feedback for modification of pelvic motion during gait.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
